node.text:
#architectsvision 
Who’d you bring? 
The Hideout Horizon  @hideoutbali is (as indicated) located in the eastern part of Bali near the volcano, Mount Agung. // Photos by @thefreedomcomplex 
.
a truly magical off-grid eco bamboo home hidden in the Balinese jungles high up in the mountains of Gunung Agung volcano. Due to its remote location, it is situated far away from the city life and therefore perfect for adventurous souls. The all-bamboo house has two floors including a breezy outdoor living area with a hammock, a wardrobe, a bathroom, and a beautiful authentic pool.

The Phú Yên House It is designed by Story Architecture and is located in Phu Yen, Vietnam // Photos by @minqbui.photography 
.
a summer retreat on the Vietnamese countryside for a family with children. The space of the bedroom and living room, kitchen and dining room are separated, and linked together by a green courtyard, making the spaces in the house airy and accessible. With the best nature, the yard and green spaces also become a fun area for the children and their friends.

node.text:
#architectsvision.
kyoto house / @aman_kyoto is designed by Kerry Hill Architects // Photos by @benrich__.
 .
In the historic and cultural ancient capital, Kyoto, Aman’s secluded 80-acre property creates a respite in the heart of one of Japan's most visited cities. With a blend of authentic, traditional ryokan hospitality and contemporary spaces, each room captures a contemporary, minimalistic style with a nod to the quintessential ryokan feel; walls of windows bringing the outside in to spacious, light-filled interiors

#architectsvision.
the Victoria Residence /The house is designed by @electricbowery // Photos by @laurejoliet.
.
draws inspiration from the long history of artists who have traditionally sought retreat in the lush, sanctuary-like area in Venice Beach. With a series of Zen outdoor spaces that allow the seamless transition between indoor and outdoor living, the home is a tranquil dwelling perfect for the owners’ deep-rooted passion for art, yoga, and meditation.

node.text:
#architectsvision.
Thoughts on this home? 
‘Bring To Light’  The house is designed by @staffordarchitecture and is located in Sydney, Australia // Photos by @smartanson.
.
a terrace house in Sydney’s Darling Point, transformed from its former dark and pokey dual occupancy into a bright and contemporary home for its owners. To allow views towards the Rushcutters Bay from even the furthest depths of the house, the interior was entirely opened up and carved to create soaring ceilings and voids.
